{
  "text": "In this study, the disturbance torque is assumed to be perturbed by an oscillatory disturbance with angular frequency ω 0 . The plant system of the friction-free DOB is shown in Fig. 3. In Fig. 3 , the dynamics of the oscillatory element is modeled by using a second-order system, where J m denotes the motor inertia, K t denotes the torque coefficient, I m denotes the motor torque current, and ω m denotes the motor speed. T dis is the disturbance torque given by a the step function expressed by [CITATION_1] , and T dis is the oscillatory torque expressed in (9). ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "31921404"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "31921404": {
      "title": "Asymptotic analysis of the dither effect in systems with friction",
      "abstract": "In this paper we revisited the effect of dither signal in servo-drives with dynamic friction. In opposition to existing results based on memoryless friction models, the average effect of friction can be qualified in terms of amplitude and frequency of the dither signal. This result is obtained by a new proposed modification of singular perturbation theory that, in particular, allows the stabilizing effect of the dither to be rigorously proved. Experimental results showing the stick-slip extinction are also presented."
    }
  }
}